description.narrative: Output 3.1. By 2020, an integrated national child protection system that prevents and responds to violence, exploitation, abuse, discrimination and neglect and ensures the care of vulnerable children., which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Protection And Emergencies, Child Protection Systems, Child Protection â€“ General, Child Protection â€“ Strengthen Families And Communities, Cross-Sectoral Adolescent Development, Data And Child Protection, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Hiv Prevention, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid), Protect, Care And Support Children And Families Affected By Hiv, Violence, Exploitation And Abuse. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 3. A comprehensive and functional national and subnational system that prevents gender-based violence and violence against children and delivers quality and equitable response services to survivors and victims.

title.narrative: Output 3.1. By 2020, an integrated national child protection system that prevents and responds to violence, exploitation, abuse,discrimination and neglect and ensures the care of vulnerable children.

description.narrative: UNICEF’s advocacy, technical and financial investments and strategic partnerships, contributed to significant progress in building an integrated national protection system, that included approval of the National Child Policy; establishment of a national multi-sectoral Child Well-Being Steering Committee; increased data use for child protection planning and budgeting; 432,165 people reached with messages on where to report SEA; 18,431,702 adolescents reached with messages on VAC and harmful practices; 66,479 children received child protection services; 2,142 children received alternative care services; 35,681 children benefitting from psychosocial support; and 3,989 para-social workers, parishchiefs and community development officers mobilized to deliver VAC/harmful practices prevention interventions. | Status:Met | As-of Date:13/01/2021
